        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer260573041" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8051516382938380886">I have read a number of Michener&apos;s books and this is one the best. I just loved how Michener introduced each period in the story by how a dig reveals artifacts in different layers (era). I particularly enjoyed the parts where the Olympic games were held - how the people observed them. There was also a fascinating chapter about the evolution of religion through the introduction of a figurine of Astarte. This book is quite educational. I recommend it to those who are interested in learning more ab</span>
  <span id="freeText8051516382938380886" style="display:none">I have read a number of Michener's books and this is one the best. I just loved how Michener introduced each period in the story by how a dig reveals artifacts in different layers (era). I particularly enjoyed the parts where the Olympic games were held - how the people observed them. There was also a fascinating chapter about the evolution of religion through the introduction of a figurine of Astarte. This book is quite educational. I recommend it to those who are interested in learning more about Israel and surrounding places.</span>
