  <span id="freeText218871549314743988" style="display:none">I read this back when I was in grade 10 and it's stuck with me all these years later. Profoundly visceral depiction of the lives, villages, towns, and cities that grow (and fall) around a single water source -- a well -- over millennia of human history.</span>
